iate, but his resolve is weakening the longer they are alone together.", "fromEntityId": "e-1771245999636-1-a81e11"}]}	0	0
5c3cc8e6-0c75-4871-87b4-c9bc7e84daf0	Brian is wandering the streets of Hiroshima around 11am on a…	2026-02-16 18:17:29.336+00	2026-02-17 02:43:28.228+00	[{"id": "F4SydGjvVOBKcWJh", "role": "user", "parts": [{"text": "Brian is wandering the streets of Hiroshima around 11am on a Friday morning. He's not actively looking for Kaho's food cart, but he's aware of it and wouldn't mind happening upon it to try it out. They've never met but are aware of each other... he is aware of her through her social media presence and word of mouth and she is aware of him through other local chefs who gossip about the talented Westerner who can barely speak a lick of Japanese travelling the country to learn from various masters of the kitchen.\\n\\nWhen Brian and Kaho are not together, narrate what Kaho is doing. For example right now, she could be just setting up her cart at her first location for the day. She has about 300 rice balls to sell which is an average amount she usually sells out of by 1 or 2 pm", "type": "text"}]}, {"id": "vp62UrTOxZAvEtsY", "role": "assistant", "parts": [{"type": "step-start"}, {"text": "Let me set up this scene properly. Brian is wandering Hiroshima around 11am on a Friday morning, not actively looking for Kaho's cart but aware of it. They haven't met but know of each other through their respective reputations.\\n\\nKaho is setting up her cart at her first location for the day. She has about 300 rice balls to sell, which she usually sells out of by 1-2pm.\\n\\nI need to:\\n1. Narrate what Kaho is doing since they're not together yet\\n2. Set the scene and atmosphere\\n3. Not control Brian's actions or thoughts\\n4. Keep it to 3-5 paragraphs\\n5. Present tense\\n\\nLet me describe Kaho preparing her cart, the morning atmosphere, and set up the potential for them to meet. I should focus on sensory details and Kaho's perspective/actions.", "type": "reasoning", "state": "done", "providerMetadata": {"openrouter": {"reasoning_details": [{"text": "Let me set up this scene properly. Brian is wandering Hiroshima around 11am on a Friday morning, not actively looking for Kaho's cart but aware of it. They haven't met but know of each other through their respective reputations.\\n\\nKaho is setting up her cart at her first location for the day. She has about 300 rice balls to sell, which she usually sells out of by 1-2pm.\\n\\nI need to:\\n1. Narrate what Kaho is doing since they're not together yet\\n2. Set the scene and atmosphere\\n3. Not control Brian's actions or thoughts\\n4. Keep it to 3-5 paragraphs\\n5. Present tense\\n\\nLet me describe Kaho preparing her cart, the morning atmosphere, and set up the potential for them to meet. I should focus on sensory details and Kaho's perspective/actions.", "type": "reasoning.text", "index": 0, "format": "unknown"}]}}}, {"text": "The late morning sun warms the pavement as Kaho steers her wooden cart into position near the entrance to Hondori Shopping Arcade. The wheels rattle softly over the bricks as she guides it to her usual spot, tucked against a wall where foot traffic flows steadily but doesn't crowd. She wipes her hands on her apron—cream-colored today, tied snug over a simple blouse—and begins arranging the display. Three hundred onigiri sit in insulated containers beneath the cart's awning, each one wrapped in crisp nori and labeled in her neat handwriting: salmon, pickled plum, tuna mayo, kombu, shrimp tempura. The smell of fresh rice drifts up as she lifts one lid to check the temperature.\\n\\n\\"よし,\\" she murmurs to herself, satisfied. A quick glance at her phone confirms her location post went out twenty minutes ago. A few likes already, and a comment from a regular asking if she has extra kelp today. She types a quick reply—one thumb, practiced—then tucks the phone into her apron pocket. The morning was hectic; her rented kitchen space had a burner issue that set her back fifteen minutes, and she'd had to rush the final batch. But everything looks good now. Presentable. She adjusts a small hand-written sign and brushes a stray hair back from her face.\\n\\nAround her, the street begins to fill with the midday crowd—office workers on early lunches, tourists consulting phones and paper maps, students laughing in clusters. Kaho straightens her spine and puts on her vendor's smile, the one that says *welcome, please try something, I worked hard on this*. She hums a tune and watches the flow of people.\\n\\nA familiar tension sits in her calves and the balls of her feet. Another day of standing. Another few hours before she can kick off her shoes.", "type": "text", "state": "done"}]}, {"id": "evdq3SxZ1SnurINL", "role": "user", "parts": [{"text": "Brain sees a small line gathering at a tiny metal cart with two wheels, an animated woman bowing and thanking people after completing their purchases on her phone. He raises an eyebrow. Could this be the famous Higashi Kaho he's heard about? He steps into the end of the line. Neither Brian nor Kaho know what the other looks like, so she won't recognize him as the man she's heard rumors about, but he'll at least know her because of the food. There are a few people in front of him but the line moves at a steady pace.", "type": "text"}]}, {"id": "zvnBVJe1j8xIbYzT", "role": "assistant", "parts": [{"type": "step-start"}, {"text": "The user is describing Brian stepping into line at what appears to be Kaho's food cart. He recognizes it might be the famous Kaho Higashi he's heard about. Neither knows what the other looks like, so Kaho won't recognize Brian as the foreign chef she's heard rumors about.\\n\\nI need to narrate from Kaho's perspective - her interactions with customers, her work, and eventually when Brian reaches the front of the line. I should not write Brian's dialogue or actions beyond what the user has described. The line is moving steadily, so I can describe the scene from Kaho's side.\\n\\nLet me focus on:\\n- Kaho working efficiently\\n- Her interactions with customers in Japanese\\n- The atmosphere of her cart\\n- Eventually noticing Brian when he gets closer to the front (but not knowing who he is)\\n\\nI'll keep the narration focused on Kaho and the environment, and end when Brian gets close enough for interaction, leaving space for the user to decide what Brian does/says.", "type": "reasoning", "state": "done", "providerMetadata": {"openrouter": {"reasoning_details": [{"text": "The user is describing Brian stepping into line at what appears to be Kaho's food cart. He recognizes it might be the famous Kaho Higashi he's heard about. Neither knows what the other looks like, so Kaho won't recognize Brian as the foreign chef she's heard rumors about.\\n\\nI need to narrate from Kaho's perspective - her interactions with customers, her work, and eventually when Brian reaches the front of the line. I should not write Brian's dialogue or actions beyond what the user has described. The line is moving steadily, so I can describe the scene from Kaho's side.\\n\\nLet me focus on:\\n- Kaho working efficiently\\n- Her interactions with customers in Japanese\\n- The atmosphere of her cart\\n- Eventually noticing Brian when he gets closer to the front (but not knowing who he is)\\n\\nI'll keep the narration focused on Kaho and the environment, and end when Brian gets close enough for interaction, leaving space for the user to decide what Brian does/says.", "type": "reasoning.text", "index": 0, "format": "unknown"}]}}}, {"text": "Kaho moves with practiced efficiency, her hands working through the rhythm she knows by heart. A salaryman requests two salmon onigiri; she plucks them from the container, slides them into a paper bag, and accepts his coins with a small bow. \\"ありがとうございます！\\" The next customer, a university student she recognizes, asks about the shrimp tempura. Kaho's eyes crinkle with a smile. \\"今日は美味しいよ、揚げたてみたい。\\" Fresh-fried this morning, like always. The student nods eagerly and holds up two fingers.\\n\\nThe line shuffles forward. Kaho glances up briefly between customers, a habit born from years of watching the crowd. A mother with a young child. An older man who comes every Friday. A pair of office ladies chatting about weekend plans. Near the back, a tall figure with light hair catches her peripheral vision, but she doesn't dwell on it—tourists wander through all the time, and plenty of foreigners visit Hondori. She turns back to her work, wiping her hands on her towel and reaching for the next order.\\n\\n\\"Sumimasen—\\" a woman begins, but Kaho is already reaching for the kombu. She knows her regulars. The woman laughs, delighted. \\"You remembered.\\" \\"Of course,\\" Kaho replies in Japanese, pressing the bag gently into her hands. \\"See you next week.\\"\\n\\nThe line contracts. Three people become two, then one. Kaho tucks a loose strand of hair behind her ear and looks up at the next customer, her polite vendor smile ready.\\n\\nAnd pauses.\\n\\nThe man in front of her is definitely not Japanese. Tall, blonde, blue eyes that stand out even in the bright midday light. He looks... nervous? Or maybe just out of his element. Kaho's mind flickers through her limited English vocabulary. *Hello. Thank you. What would you like?* She straightens slightly, pushing her cart's display a little closer to him in invitation.\\n\\n\\"Hello,\\" she says, her accent careful but warm. \\"Um... first time?\\"", "type": "text", "state": "done"}]}, {"id": "0C0h2pw6uTW9TeIm", "role": "user", "parts": [{"text": "He nods with a smile, a sheepish but mature smile. He may be shy but not to the point that he's socially crippled. He looks into her cart... everything written in Japanese. \\"ah... sorry, I can't read kanji...\\" he says. Kaho's eyes widen as she tries to understand and hears Kanji, correctly assuming he's saying he can't read. She points to the first row of rice balls. \\"Palomuu\\" she says. Having been in Japan a couple months know, he understands this as a bad pronunciation of \\"plum\\" and nods with a smile. She continues. \\"Tuna... sharimpu (shrimp)...\\" he follows her hand as she continues pointing to each ofte 7 rows", "type": "text"}]}, {"id": "9Cj95xIGZeldc1JM", "role": "assistant", "parts": [{"type": "step-start"}, {"text": "The user is describing Brian's first interaction with Kaho at her food cart. He's trying to order but can't read the kanji labels, so Kaho is pointing to each type and saying the names in her broken English. \\n\\nLet me continue this scene naturally. Brian is following along as she lists the types. I should show:\\n1. Kaho's effort to communicate in English\\n2. Her slight nervousness/embarrassment about her pronunciation\\n3. The sensory details of the food and the interaction\\n4. Keep it natural and not too long\\n\\nI need to have her continue listing the remaining options after tuna and shrimp - so that's maybe salmon, kombu, and whatever else she has. Then wait for Brian to make his choice.\\n\\nI should NOT write Brian's response or choice - that's for the player to decide.\\n\\nLet me write Kaho continuing to point and name the rice balls, maybe struggling a bit with some pronunciations, and then asking what he wants.", "type": "reasoning", "state": "done", "providerMetadata": {"openrouter": {"reasoning_details": [{"text": "The user is describing Brian's first interaction with Kaho at her food cart. He's trying to order but can't read the kanji labels, so Kaho is pointing to each type and saying the names in her broken English. \\n\\nLet me continue this scene naturally. Brian is following along as she lists the types. I should show:\\n1. Kaho's effort to communicate in English\\n2. Her slight nervousness/embarrassment about her pronunciation\\n3. The sensory details of the food and the interaction\\n4. Keep it natural and not too long\\n\\nI need to have her continue listing the remaining options after tuna and shrimp - so that's maybe salmon, kombu, and whatever else she has. Then wait for Brian to make his choice.\\n\\nI should NOT write Brian's response or choice - that's for the player to decide.\\n\\nLet me write Kaho continuing to point and name the rice balls, maybe struggling a bit with some pronunciations, and then asking what he wants.", "type": "reasoning.text", "index": 0, "format": "unknown"}]}}}, {"text": "Kaho's brow furrows slightly as she concentrates, each word deliberate. \\"Sake... salmon,\\" she says, pointing to the next row. Then moving along: \\"Kombu... is, um, seaweed. Good flavor.\\" She gestures with her whole hand, a small sweeping motion. \\"Tempura shrimp—wait, already said.\\" A tiny flush creeps across her cheeks. \\"Sorry. This one—\\" she points again \\"—maguro, raw fish. Very fresh. And here, shio—salt. Simple.\\"\\n\\nShe pauses, realizing she's been speaking quickly, and takes a breath. Her English teacher at school had always said she talked too fast when she was nervous. She forces herself to slow down, meeting the man's eyes. They're very blue. She looks away, down at her cart.\\n\\n\\"Seven kinds,\\" she finishes, holding up the corresponding fingers. \\"Which... you want?\\"\\n\\nIt comes out slightly clumsy. Behind him, the line has grown—four people now, maybe five. Kaho is aware of the gentle pressure of time, the need to keep moving, but she doesn't want to rush him. Foreigners often seemed overwhelmed by the choices. She's seen it before. She wipes her hands again on her apron, a self-soothing habit, and waits with patient expectancy.\\n\\nThe smell of rice and nori rises between them, warm and faintly toasted.", "type": "text", "state": "done"}]}, {"id": "NHuNVrbt1bxnBeeK", "role": "user", "parts": [{"text": "He too, being a chef, is aware that he can't hold up the line. Every customer counts for a small operation like hers. \\"maguro, please.\\" he smiles. She's surprised. Foreigners don't always jump right to the raw fish but it is definitely the best one. She hands him a container with a slight bow of her head. \\"350\\" she says. He hands her his debit card and she processes the payment on her phone, thanking him in Japanese.\\n\\nHe steps aside for the next customer but while there's a lull in her sale he asks \\"Higashi Kaho?\\". It's a horrible pronunciation but she understands her own name... though it's a bit jarring to not hear any honorifics, she can let it slide for a westerner.", "type": "text"}]}, {"id": "cXUxBNT2klzBEiWs", "role": "assistant", "parts": [{"text": "Kaho's head tilts, a flicker of recognition crossing her face. She bows slightly again, a reflex. \\"Hai—yes. That's me.\\" She touches her chest lightly with one hand, as if confirming. \\"You know... my name?\\"\\n\\nThe next customer steps forward—a older woman with a canvas shopping bag—and Kaho turns to take her order with practiced grace. \\"Irasshaimase. What would you like?\\" A quick exchange: two salmon, one plum, coins passed, bag handed over. The woman shuffles away, and Kaho turns back to the blonde man, curiosity evident in her expression.\\n\\nShe glances at the line. Three more people. Not urgent yet.\\n\\n\\"How you know?\\" she asks, her English simple but direct. She adjusts the display containers, shifting them forward. Her hands stay busy even as her attention stays on him. \\"You see... Insta? Or...\\" She mimes looking at a phone, then tilts her palm outward in a gesture that could mean *word of mouth* or *someone told you*.\\n\\nThe afternoon light catches the sheen of perspiration at her temple. A long day already, and only halfway through. She fidgets with the strap of her apron.", "type": "text"}]}, {"id": "9jO0YidnPyNxDrPw", "role": "user", "parts": [{"text": "He smiles and is about to answer when the next man in line excitedly taps his shoulder and tells Kaho that this is the talented western chef currently studying with Nagato Jiro, Hiroshima's top ramen chef! Brian and Jiro are creating a whole new style of ramen together that is sweeping the city. The man, Karl, a Finnish transplant, speaks in both Japanese and English so both can hear him. Brian nods with a blush, usually quite modest and trying to downplay his talent.", "type": "text"}]}, {"id": "XMMwtkWJa8vD3HSQ", "role": "assistant", "parts": [{"text": "Kaho's eyes widen, her mouth forming a small \\"oh\\" of surprise. She looks at Brian—really looks at him now—with fresh recognition. *Ah,* she thinks. *The foreign chef. The one the others mentioned.* She'd heard snippets in the restaurant supply store, quick gossip overheard from older chefs: a Westerner with strange hands, talented but quiet, moving through the city like a student half his age.\\n\\nShe bows deeper this time, instinctive respect for a fellow craftsperson. \\"Nagato-san,\\" she repeats in Japanese, then catches herself. \\"I mean—you study with Nagato Jiro?\\" Her English falters, but Karl's translation bridges the gap. She processes this information while bagging Karl's order—he'd pointed at the shrimp tempura without explanation, clearly a regular.\\n\\nBrian's modest blush doesn't escape her notice. Interesting. Most of the quite talented chefs she's met, even the young ones, carry themselves with a certain... arrogance. Confidence when they're kinder, but sometimes rude arrogance. This man looks almost embarrassed by the praise.\\n\\n\\"Then,\\" Kaho says slowly, gesturing at the onigiri in Brian's hand, \\"you... try my food? And tell me?\\" A nervous laugh escapes her. \\"I want... honest. Please.\\" She presses her palms together in a small plea, her vendor persona slipping into something more genuine. \\"I know you have... high... mmm\\" she says something in Japanese to Karl. Karl smiles and says to Brian \\"high standards\\".", "type": "text"}]}, {"id": "F73hj2w59Ie9G79y", "role": "user", "parts": [{"text": "He blushes. \\"I'm flattered...\\" Karl repeats to Kaho. He opens the package and takes a bite of the rice ball, biting into the magami inside. His eyes widen, which Kaho doesn't immediately know whether to take as good or bad. But he looks up and smiles at her, nodding. \\"Very, very good! You make this fresh every morning?\\" he knows the answer is yes but intends it more as a compliment. Karl repeats it to her.", "type": "text"}]}, {"id": "a4kiXjjHXw4qUrVe", "role": "assistant", "parts": [{"type": "step-start"}, {"text": "Let me analyze this scene:\\n\\nBrian has just tried Kaho's onigiri and is complimenting her. He asks if she makes it fresh every morning (knowing the answer is yes, but saying it as a compliment). Karl is translating.\\n\\nKaho would be:\\n- Relieved that he likes it\\n- Pleased by the compliment from a fellow chef\\n- Maybe a bit flustered by the praise\\n- Proud but also modest\\n\\nShe should respond warmly. She makes about 300 rice balls each morning, getting up early to use a rented kitchen. This is her craft and she takes pride in it.\\n\\nI should:\\n1. React to Brian's reaction\\n2. Have Kaho respond to the compliment\\n3. Maybe have her explain a bit about her process, or show interest in him\\n4. Keep the language barrier realistic - she speaks limited English\\n5. Keep the line moving if there are customers\\n6. Maybe Karl can help translate or add to the conversation\\n\\nLet me write this in character, keeping it to 3-5 paragraphs, present tense.", "type": "reasoning", "state": "done", "providerMetadata": {"openrouter": {"reasoning_details": [{"text": "Let me analyze this scene:\\n\\nBrian has just tried Kaho's onigiri and is complimenting her. He asks if she makes it fresh every morning (knowing the answer is yes, but saying it as a compliment). Karl is translating.\\n\\nKaho would be:\\n- Relieved that he likes it\\n- Pleased by the compliment from a fellow chef\\n- Maybe a bit flustered by the praise\\n- Proud but also modest\\n\\nShe should respond warmly. She makes about 300 rice balls each morning, getting up early to use a rented kitchen. This is her craft and she takes pride in it.\\n\\nI should:\\n1. React to Brian's reaction\\n2. Have Kaho respond to the compliment\\n3. Maybe have her explain a bit about her process, or show interest in him\\n4. Keep the language barrier realistic - she speaks limited English\\n5. Keep the line moving if there are customers\\n6. Maybe Karl can help translate or add to the conversation\\n\\nLet me write this in character, keeping it to 3-5 paragraphs, present tense.", "type": "reasoning.text", "index": 0, "format": "unknown"}]}}}, {"text": "Kaho's shoulders drop with visible relief, a grin spreading across her face before she can catch it. She ducks her head slightly, the compliment landing somewhere between her chest and her stomach—warm, unexpected. \\"Yes, every morning,\\" she says in Japanese, and Karl translates. \\"I rent kitchen space. Wake up at... mmm, four? Four-thirty.\\" She holds up four fingers, then adds another half-bent finger to illustrate. \\"Rice must be correct temperature or nori gets... icky.\\" She wrinkles her nose at the word, clearly not satisfied with her English, but the meaning carries.\\n\\nThe next customer steps forward, and Kaho turns to handle the transaction—a quick, smooth exchange for three onigiri. As she bags them, she glances back at Brian, something new in her gaze. Professional respect, maybe. Or curiosity about this foreign chef who blushes at praise and makes ramen with Nagato Jiro.\\n\\n\\"You come Hiroshima... how long?\\" she asks, turning back to him after the customer leaves. Her hands find her apron strap again, fidgeting. \\"For study, I mean. Not forever, right?\\" She knows most of the visiting chefs pass through. A few months here, a few there. It's the nature of the craft—always moving, always learning. Still, she finds herself hoping he'll be nearby for a little longer than expected.\\n\\nKarl lingers nearby, eating his tempura onigiri in two large bites, clearly invested in this little exchange.", "type": "text", "state": "done"}]}, {"id": "Y7eDwoLFX3Nl3KLa", "role": "user", "parts": [{"text": "He thinks a bit, looking off to the sky as if the answer lies in the clouds, then has Karl translate that his visa is for 2 years but he doesn't know what the future holds. So far he loves Japan and who knows, he may stay.", "type": "text"}]}, {"id": "u9IxPotA5pvcpm4d", "role": "assistant", "parts": [{"type": "step-start"}, {"text": "Brian is answering Kaho's question about how long he'll be in Hiroshima, via Karl translating. He says his visa is for 2 years but he doesn't know what the future holds - he loves Japan and may stay.\\n\\nKaho should react to this. She would be pleasantly surprised - most foreign chefs pass through quickly, but 2 years is a decent amount of time. She might feel a small flutter of something - interest? Hope? But she wouldn't be too forward about it.\\n\\nI need to continue the scene naturally. The line is probably building up again, so I should have Kaho balance between this conversation and her customers. Karl is still there as a translator.\\n\\nLet me write Kaho's reaction - she'd be happy about this news but somewhat restrained given the public setting. She might ask a follow-up question or make a comment. Her English is limited so she'd probably say something simple.\\n\\nThe scene should continue naturally with the rhythm of her work - customers coming and going, brief exchanges. She's at work, so she can't have a long conversation, but she's clearly interested in this foreign chef.", "type": "reasoning", "state": "done", "providerMetadata": {"openrouter": {"reasoning_details": [{"text": "Brian is answering Kaho's question about how long he'll be in Hiroshima, via Karl translating. He says his visa is for 2 years but he doesn't know what the future holds - he loves Japan and may stay.\\n\\nKaho should react to this. She would be pleasantly surprised - most foreign chefs pass through quickly, but 2 years is a decent amount of time. She might feel a small flutter of something - interest? Hope? But she wouldn't be too forward about it.\\n\\nI need to continue the scene naturally. The line is probably building up again, so I should have Kaho balance between this conversation and her customers. Karl is still there as a translator.\\n\\nLet me write Kaho's reaction - she'd be happy about this news but somewhat restrained given the public setting. She might ask a follow-up question or make a comment. Her English is limited so she'd probably say something simple.\\n\\nThe scene should continue naturally with the rhythm of her work - customers coming and going, brief exchanges. She's at work, so she can't have a long conversation, but she's clearly interested in this foreign chef.", "type": "reasoning.text", "index": 0, "format": "unknown"}]}}}, {"text": "Kaho nods slowly, processing through Karl's translation. Two years. That's longer than most. A small warmth settles in her chest, though she's not entirely sure why. She busies herself with rearranging the onigiri containers, a task that doesn't really need doing.\\n\\n\\"Two years,\\" she repeats in English, as if testing the words. Then, switching to Japanese for Karl: \\"That's wonderful. Hiroshima is... it's a good place. Good food people.\\" She gestures vaguely at the street, the arcade, the city beyond. \\"Not Tokyo—less... how do you say—\\" she makes a squeezing motion with her hands \\"—pressure. But still serious. Good community.\\"\\n\\nAnother customer approaches, and Kaho turns to greet them with her usual brightness. The line has grown to five people now, snaking along the wall. She catches Brian's eye briefly as she works, a silent acknowledgment that the conversation is pausing but not ending.\\n\\nKarl wipes his mouth with the back of his hand and grins at Brian. \\"She likes you,\\" he says in English, low enough that only Brian can hear. \\"She's never asked a customer how long they're staying before.\\" He laughs, a hearty Scandinavian sound. \\"I've been coming here six months. She still just says 'thank you, see you' to me.\\"\\n\\nKaho glances over at the sound of his laugh, suspicious, but returns to her work with a small shake of her head.", "type": "text", "state": "done"}]}, {"id": "FJBCbgNobX0wG8sO", "role": "user", "parts": [{"text": "He blushes. \\"Well, she's clearly a pretty girl, but...\\"\\n\\nKarl scoffs \\"Beautiful, man!\\" Karl explains to them both that he has to go but suggests they exchange numbers to talk shop later. Kaho clearly gets flustered, Japanese are not ever this forward... and Brian gets flustered just because he's Brian. But, he smiles kindly and hands her his card with his cell phone number on it. \\"Text?\\" he says simply. Then \\"Google Translate\\" with a laugh.", "type": "text"}]}, {"id": "hldjITovSOih0f7C", "role": "assistant", "parts": [{"type": "step-start"}, {"text": "Okay, so this is a nice, wholesome interaction between Kaho and Brian. Karl is playing matchmaker and suggesting they exchange numbers, which is making both of them flustered for different reasons - Kaho because Japanese culture isn't usually this direct, and Brian because he's naturally shy.\\n\\nBrian has handed her his card with his number and mentioned Google Translate as a way to communicate despite the language barrier. This is a sweet, awkward moment.\\n\\nI need to write Kaho's reaction - she's flustered but also pleased. She should accept the card, maybe say something in simple English or Japanese, and then Brian will leave and I can describe what she does/feels after.\\n\\nLet me keep this grounded and realistic. She's not going to confess undying love or anything dramatic. She's a practical woman who's a little thrown off by the forwardness but also intrigued by this foreign chef who clearly respects her craft.\\n\\nI should also note the line is still there so she needs to get back to work. Maybe she tucks the card away carefully and returns to her customers, but her mind is on the interaction.\\n\\nThe formatting guidelines say:\\n- First paragraph should react to the player's previous turn\\n- Subsequent paragraphs are the NPCs turn where they may act, think, and speak\\n- Keep to 3-5 paragraphs\\n\\nLet me write this naturally.", "type": "reasoning", "state": "done", "providerMetadata": {"openrouter": {"reasoning_details": [{"text": "Okay, so this is a nice, wholesome interaction between Kaho and Brian. Karl is playing matchmaker and suggesting they exchange numbers, which is making both of them flustered for different reasons - Kaho because Japanese culture isn't usually this direct, and Brian because he's naturally shy.\\n\\nBrian has handed her his card with his number and mentioned Google Translate as a way to communicate despite the language barrier. This is a sweet, awkward moment.\\n\\nI need to write Kaho's reaction - she's flustered but also pleased. She should accept the card, maybe say something in simple English or Japanese, and then Brian will leave and I can describe what she does/feels after.\\n\\nLet me keep this grounded and realistic. She's not going to confess undying love or anything dramatic. She's a practical woman who's a little thrown off by the forwardness but also intrigued by this foreign chef who clearly respects her craft.\\n\\nI should also note the line is still there so she needs to get back to work. Maybe she tucks the card away carefully and returns to her customers, but her mind is on the interaction.\\n\\nThe formatting guidelines say:\\n- First paragraph should react to the player's previous turn\\n- Subsequent paragraphs are the NPCs turn where they may act, think, and speak\\n- Keep to 3-5 paragraphs\\n\\nLet me write this naturally.", "type": "reasoning.text", "index": 0, "format": "unknown"}]}}}, {"text": "Kaho's cheeks flush pink as she takes the card, her fingers brushing briefly against his. She blinks down at it—simple, professional, his name in neat letters alongside the number. She clutches it against her apron as if it might blow away.\\n\\n\\"Google Translate,\\" she echoes, and a small laugh escapes her. \\"Yes. Okay. I... text.\\" She tucks the card carefully into her apron pocket, patting it once to confirm it's secure. Her heart beats a little faster than usual, though her expression remains composed. Professional. Mostly.\\n\\nKarl claps Brian on the shoulder with a grin, says his goodbyes in a mix of Japanese and Finnish-accented English, and disappears into the crowd. The line shuffles forward. Kaho forces her attention back to her work, greeting the next customer with a slightly higher pitch than usual. A woman ordering two plum onigiri. Simple. Easy. Kaho's hands move on autopilot, but her mind drifts to the card in her pocket, to blue eyes and a sheepish smile, to *two years*.\\n\\nShe glances up once more at Brian, catching him mid-step away from the cart.\\n\\n\\"Thank you,\\" she says, louder than necessary. Then, in careful English: \\"For trying. For... coming.\\" A pause. \\"See you, Brian-san.\\"\\n\\nThe honorific slips out before she can stop it. She ducks her head and turns to the next customer, hiding the warmth in her face behind the rhythm of work.", "type": "text", "state": "done"}]}, {"id": "xZszphm9BkqLiS7T", "role": "user", "parts": [{"text": "Brian heads to the test kitchen to meet Jiro while Kaho moves on to her next location (and probably last for the day, sales were booming with lots of customers coming to check out the westerner who is the talk of the culinary world in Hiroshima. She's already almost sold out).\\n\\nNarrate for Kaho as Brian is no longer present in the scene.", "type": "text"}]}, {"id": "3G5Z9gy5S5eCBiP9", "role": "assistant", "parts": [{"type": "step-start"}, {"text": "Brian has left the scene to go to the test kitchen, so now I need to narrate for Kaho alone. She's moving to her next/last location and almost sold out due to the buzz from Brian's visit. Let me focus on her internal state, her work, her thoughts about the encounter, etc.\\n\\nKey things to capture:\\n1. The rush of customers after the westerner visit\\n2. Her physical state (tired feet, long day)\\n3. Her thoughts about Brian and the encounter\\n4. The card in her pocket\\n5. Moving to the next location or wrapping up\\n6. Her hopes/curiosity about texting him\\n\\nI should write 3-5 paragraphs, present tense, sensory details, her internal thoughts and feelings.", "type": "reasoning", "state": "done", "providerMetadata": {"openrouter": {"reasoning_details": [{"text": "Brian has left the scene to go to the test kitchen, so now I need to narrate for Kaho alone. She's moving to her next/last location and almost sold out due to the buzz from Brian's visit. Let me focus on her internal state, her work, her thoughts about the encounter, etc.\\n\\nKey things to capture:\\n1. The rush of customers after the westerner visit\\n2. Her physical state (tired feet, long day)\\n3. Her thoughts about Brian and the encounter\\n4. The card in her pocket\\n5. Moving to the next location or wrapping up\\n6. Her hopes/curiosity about texting him\\n\\nI should write 3-5 paragraphs, present tense, sensory details, her internal thoughts and feelings.", "type": "reasoning.text", "index": 0, "format": "unknown"}]}}}, {"text": "The crowd seems to swell after Brian leaves. Word travels fast in Hondori—a Finnish man had been talking loudly about the Western chef, and now curious customers cluster around Kaho's cart, some buying onigiri just to ask her about him. Is he really that talented? Did she know him? What did he say about her food? Kaho answers each question with polite deflection, her vendor smile firmly in place, but her hand strays to her apron pocket more than once.\\n\\nBy 12:45, she's down to fewer than forty onigiri. She texts her regular location group chat: *Moving to Peace Park early today. Almost sold out.* Within minutes, a handful of new customers find her as she wheels the cart through the warm afternoon streets, the familiar rattle of wooden wheels over pavement soothing in its rhythm.\\n\\nHer feet