m—talented, humble, kind—living a block away, and she'd had no idea.\\n\\n\\"Small world,\\" she says in English, a phrase she remembers from a movie. She gestures between them, then at the street. \\"We walk same streets. Maybe... pass each other before? And not know?\\"\\n\\nThe cart wheels over a crack in the pavement. Kaho steers slightly left, guiding them around a pothole. Her left foot protests with a dull throb, and she shifts her weight to her right, hoping the movement looks natural rather than pained. Sweat prickles at the back of her neck.\\n\\n\\"Convenience store below me has... many onigiri,\\" she jokes, gesturing ahead. \\"Factory kind. Not good like mine.\\" She scrunches her nose. \\"But sometimes I am lazy. I buy anyway. Don't tell anyone.\\" She mimes zipping her lips shut, then laughs at herself.\\n\\nA delivery scooter buzzes past. The smell of exhaust mixes with the lingering scent of rice from her cart and something floral from a nearby shop. Kaho finds herself glancing at Brian's profile as they walk—his blonde hair catching the sunlight, his easy posture despite the cart's weight.\\n\\n\\"Close now,\\" she murmurs. \\"Almost there.\\"", "type": "text", "state": "done"}]}, {"id": "GfwDJs8wVPeasBqo", "role": "user", "parts": [{"text": "He laughs and mimes zipping his mouth too. \\"I have been to that store, we probably have seen each other. Funny to think.\\" he looks ahead at the store, and her apartment, approaching. He feels a little disappointed about it. Even though they can't speak to each other very well, he likes her.", "type": "text"}]}, {"id": "gq1WjzUCwizpAwnp", "role": "assistant", "parts": [{"type": "step-start"}, {"text": "The user wants me to narrate as Kaho, since Brian is leaving the scene. Let me focus on Kaho's perspective, her feelings, and what happens next.\\n\\nKey points:\\n- They're approaching her apartment above the convenience store\\n- Brian likes her but feels disappointed the walk is ending\\n- Kaho should have