een them.", "type": "reasoning.text", "index": 0, "format": "unknown"}]}}}, {"text": "*Pretty girl.*\\n\\nThe words land somewhere in Kaho's chest and stay there, warm and startling. She ducks her head, focusing intently on the vegetables he's pulled from the fridge—a leek, some shiitake, a piece of salmon wrapped in paper. Her ears feel hot. Her socks feel damp. She's acutely aware of both at once.\\n\\n\\"Thank you,\\" she manages, her voice smaller than intended. She doesn't know the English for *you shouldn't say things like that* or *that's too forward* or *my grandfather would have a stroke.* So she just stands there, hands clasped in front of her apron, watching him arrange ingredients on the counter.\\n\\nThe elbow nudge lingers in her memory. Such a small gesture. In Japan, it would mean something. Here, in his kitchen, with his broken Japanese and his pretty girl—it means something too. She's just not sure what yet.\\n\\n\\"What are you making?\\" she asks, stepping closer to watch. Professional curiosity. Safe ground. Her shoulder brushes his arm and she doesn't pull away. \\"Can I help? I am... assistant today. Student.\\" She grins up at him, trying to regain her footing. \\"You teach. I learn. Fair trade, yes?\\"", "type": "text", "state": "done"}]}, {"id": "LULbodKFDclFJYsP", "role": "user", "parts": [{"text": "He nods, his eyes showing that he's impressed at her willingness to learn. He hands her a chef's knife that probably cost several hundred US dollars and tasks her with chopping the leek and shiitake. When she starts chopping rapidly with even, measured cuts while he preps the salmon, he lets out an impressed \\"aah!\\" she looks up and he nods at her. \\"Very good. Skilled\\" he smiles.", "type": "text"}]}, {"id": "8oUvmrfYpihKo7yy", "role": "assistant", "parts": [{"text": "Kaho straightens slightly at his praise, a flush of pride warming her chest. Nobody has actually *seen* her cook before. She always does it before anyone else gets to the restaurant, and her ex boyfriend only liked fast food. She returns to the cutting board, her knife moving in quick, precise arcs. The leek falls into even ribbons. The shiitake separate into uniform slices. Muscle memory from thousands of mornings in Yamamoto-san's kitchen, from years of shaping rice balls before the sun rises.\\n\\n\\"Practice,\\" she says simply, not looking up. \\"Every day. Many years.\\" She taps the knife against the board, clearing the blade. \\"You learn from Nagato Jiro. I learn from... repetition.\\" A small laugh. \\"Different teachers.\\"\\n\\nThe kitchen fills with the smell of salmon as Brian sears it, the flesh hitting hot oil with a satisfying hiss. Kaho's stomach responds with another growl, and this time she doesn't apologize—just presses her hand against it and shakes her head at herself.\\n\\nShe finishes the mushrooms and steps back, wiping her hands on her apron. Her shoulder brushes his arm again. Closer now. She can smell the faint remnants of restaurant kitchen on him—dash, sesame, smoke—layered beneath something cleaner. Soap, maybe. Shampoo. And a pleasant citrusy cologne. Her perfume is long since worn through.", "type": "text"}]}, {"id": "wHxign1Xmlan1WT3", "role": "user", "parts": [{"text": "He nods, impressed. \\"Don't need expensive cooking school to be good, just passion\\" he smiles. \\"So... I read on your Insta that your grandpa built your cart by hand? He was an architect or something?\\" She hears cart but the rest is a blur. \\"Ahh...\\" she blushes as she tries to piece the syllables together. He smiles and shakes his head. \\"Sorry, sorry. Too much.\\" he types the questions back into his phone and lets her read the translation.", "type": "text"}]}, {"id": "WvRXbobrqTonC1zE", "role": "assistant", "parts": [{"type": "step-start"}, {"text": "The user wants me to continue the scene where Brian asks Kaho about her grandfather and the cart. He's typed the question into his phone for her to read.\\n\\nI need to stay 