a moment, letting the coolness seep into her warmed skin.\\n\\nFrom her perch on the stool, she watches him plate the sashimi. Each piece laid with intention, the angle precise, the garnish placed like brushstrokes on a canvas. Restaurant quality. Better than restaurant quality. This is the food of someone who *loves* what he does, who sees beauty in a slice of raw fish and refuses to let it be ordinary.\\n\\nHer eyes sting slightly. She blinks it away, tells herself it's the steam from the rice cooker, the heat of the kitchen.\\n\\n\\"Brian-san,\\" she says quietly. \\"Why... why you cook for me? You don't know me. We met yesterday.\\" She tilts her head, genuinely curious. \\"Most people... they don't do this. Invite stranger. Cook. Be kind.\\" She gestures vaguely with her free hand. \\"Why?\\"", "type": "text", "state": "done"}]}, {"id": "XSPBqF3TFbif6uMy", "role": "user", "parts": [{"text": "He blushes more visibly now, wiping his hands on his apron to buy himself time to think. He decides to text her, holding his phone up as a question of *is this okay* and she nods, taking out her phone with a smile. He's cute like this. So worried about my comfort, she thinks. He types a lot, but she waits patiently until her phone vibrates.\\n\\n*brian: At first I just wanted to see your food, you are very popular on social media, even in America. Then I saw you and... you are very beautiful girl. I don't know if this is okay to say to you. I make a lot of mistakes in Japan with my behavior but I try to be right. Even if just friend, I like to get to know you. Very sweet voice. Kind face. Very good onigiri* he adds a smile to tell her that last bit is a shy joke. She reads the whole thing twice, blushing, but her smile is unmistakable. Still, she can't be too forward... wouldn't even know how.", "type": "text"}]}, {"id": "EgqAzeUeOsdszqWR", "role": "assistant", "parts": [{"type": "step-start"}, {"text": "The user wants me to continue the scene where Kaho has just received a