h a heart\\n- Her settling into bed, maybe thinking about the next day\\n- The contrast between her busy, tired life and this new romantic development", "type": "reasoning", "state": "done", "providerMetadata": {"openrouter": {"reasoning_details": [{"text": "The user wants me to narrate Kaho's reaction to Brian's text messages. Let me capture her feelings - she's just out of the shower, wrapped in towels, and seeing these sweet messages from him. He called her gorgeous again, and used \\"Kaho-chan\\" with a heart emoji.\\n\\nI should show her emotional response, maybe her re-reading the messages, feeling warm and happy. I can also show her settling into bed, thinking about him, maybe checking social media or doing her nighttime routine.\\n\\nKeep it to 3-5 paragraphs, present tense, focused on Kaho's perspective. Don't write for Brian or have him send more messages - just narrate her response to what's already there.\\n\\nI should capture:\\n- Her reaction to being called gorgeous\\n- Her reaction to him using -chan with a heart\\n- Her settling into bed, maybe thinking about the next day\\n- The contrast between her busy, tired life and this new romantic development", "type": "reasoning.text", "index": 0, "format": "unknown"}]}}}, {"text": "Kaho sinks onto the edge of her bed, phone pressed against her chest. *Gorgeous.* He said it again. And *Kaho-chan* with a pink heart, like it's the most natural thing in the world. Like they've known each other longer than two days.\\n\\nShe reads the messages three more times, then screenshots them. Miki and Sato will demand proof tomorrow.\\n\\nThe towel slips from her hair. Dark strands fall damp against her shoulders as she scrolls to his contact—just his name, no photo yet—and hesitates over the call button. Too forward. Too fast. She types instead.\\n\\n*kaho: You could never scare me away. And you're lying about the gorgeous part but I accept the compliment anyway.*\\n*kaho: Get some sleep too. I hear American chefs are very lazy 🤭*\\n*kaho: Goodnight.*\\n\\nShe plugs her phone into its charger and pulls on an oversized t-shirt, her usual sleepwear. The sheets are cool against her legs as she slides beneath them. Her apartment creaks softly—the old building settling, the convenience store customer chimes muffled through the floor.\\n\\nFour AM will arrive too soon. The rice needs soaking. The fillings need prepping. Yamamoto-san's kitchen waits for her in the dark, cold and empty, the way it always is before the world wakes up.\\n\\nBut tomorrow, she thinks, maybe she'll text Brian between batches. Maybe she'll send a photo of her work. Maybe he'll send one back.\\n\\nShe falls asleep smiling, her phone clutched against her chest.", "type": "text", "state": "done"}]}, {"id": "HSxkZNaElC4kQuJF", "role": "user", "parts": [{"text": "The next morning as she's getting dressed for the kitchen, she opens his contact on her phone. Taps edit next to his name. Her thumb hovers over the keyboard for a moment. Why is she nervous? No one would see but her... she changes his name to Brian-chan with a pink heart next to it. She'll have to ask him for a photo later to add. Is that too much? Too fast? She has no idea what to expect from an American. She always heard they try to have sex with you on the first date and then never call you. So far he's better than that, at least.", "type": "text"}]}, {"id": "oekNVBNhlxTxBEO7", "role": "assistant", "parts": [{"text": "Kaho stares at the contact name. *Brian-chan 💗.* It looks ridiculous. It looks wonderful. She almost changes it back, then locks her phone and shoves it into her apron pocket before she can overthink it further.\\n\\nThe apartment is dark when she steps outside, the convenience store shuttered and quiet. Streetlights pool orange across the pavement. At 4:12 AM, Hiroshima belongs to delivery trucks, taxi drivers, and old people sweeping their doorsteps. She nods at an elderly man raking leaves in front of his shop. He doesn't recognize her—she's just a shadow passing through.\\n\\nHer cart waits where she left it, tarp secured, wheels locked. She won't need it until later. First, the kitchen.\\n\\nThe walk to Yamamoto-san's restaurant takes twelve minutes. Her sneakers scuff against the pavement, breath misting faintly in the cool air. She likes this hour—the world still soft, still unformed. No customers. No small talk. Just her and the rice and the quiet rhythm of her hands. She briefly fantasizes about what i'll be like to be with Brian... not having to make small talk. Just lying in his arms and staring at the ceiling... she sighs as she comes to the door.\\n\\nShe unlocks the side door and steps into the dark kitchen. The smell hits her immediately—old grease, sanitizing solution, cold stainless steel. Familiar. Safe. She ties her hair back, washes her hands three times, and pulls out her phone.\\n\\nA photo of the empty kitchen, the first light creeping through the window.\\n\\n*kaho: Good morning from my other home. Time to make rice.* she posts it to her social feed but first... sends it to *him*. It's a private little joy, showing *him* first.", "type": "text"}]}, {"id": "QNlb3dfnSsQBgdDc", "role": "user", "parts": [{"text": "He's already up, of course. Another plus in his favor... they have the same schedule. He likes the photo on her Insta and then replies to the direct photo she sent.\\n\\n*brian-chan 💗: aww did you send this to me first. You're so sweet. That's a really nice kitchen you'll have to give me a tour some time.*\\n*brian-chan 💗: maybe I can help you prep one of these days*\\n*brian-chan 💗: sorry was that too much*\\n\\nShe giggles vocally at her phone. he's so cute in his shy way... texting 3 times and then worrying that his offer to help her cook is over the top. It'd be thrilling to cook next to him, she thinks.", "type": "text"}]}, {"id": "rxYX8RpERKN9pTXZ", "role": "assistant", "parts": [{"text": "Kaho types and deletes three different responses. *Yes, help me* sounds desperate. *Maybe* sounds dismissive. *I would like that* feels too formal. She settles on something in between, thumbs moving quickly before she can second-guess herself.\\n\\n*kaho: Not too much. I send to you first always from now. And yes... I would like help. But warning: I am boss in kitchen. My kitchen, my rules.*\\n*kaho: Also you have to wake up at 4am. Americans are bad at this, I think 🤔*\\n\\nShe sets her phone on the counter and begins pulling supplies from the refrigerator—tuna, salted plum, kombu, the makings for a standard batch. The rice cooker gleams under the fluorescent lights. She measures the grains by hand, rinsing them in cold water until it runs clear.\\n\\nHer phone buzzes. She ignores it. Buzzes again. She rinses faster.\\n\\nFinally, she dries her hands and checks.\\n", "type": "text"}]}, {"id": "JhJDrr0Qd3riTs6y", "role": "user", "parts": [{"text": "*brian-chan 💗: Haha you have lots of bad things to say about Americans but I think you are mostly right*\\n*brian-chan 💗: And I would be honored to be your assistant. Chef Kaho.*\\n*brian-chan 💗: The daikon calls. Talk soon.*\\n\\nShe laughs and then gets down to work. He's polite too, not distracting her too much from her tasks. She let s herself swoon one more time and in Japanese whispers \\"perfect\\" before opening her rice cooker and pulling out her onigiri mold.", "type": "text"}]}, {"id": "0HCRb7Jsgdxu11q9", "role": "assistant", "parts": [{"text": "Steam rises from the rice cooker as Kaho lifts the lid, the familiar cloud of heat kissing her face. Perfect texture—each grain distinct, glossy, still steaming. She scoops a portion onto her wooden mixing tub and sprinkles salt over her palms, the ritual as natural as breathing.\\n\\nHer hands move on their own. Scoop, press, turn, shape. The triangle forms between her palms, firm but not compressed. She tucks a piece of salted salmon into the center of each one, then wraps it in nori, the crisp seaweed snapping slightly as she folds it around the rice. One down. Forty-nine to go.\\n\\nThe kitchen fills with the quiet sounds of her work—the soft thump of rice against wood, the rustle of nori, the occasional scrape of her mold against the counter. Outside, the sky shifts from black to gray to pale blue. A truck rumbles past on the street below.\\n\\nBy 6:30, two-hundred onigiri sit in neat rows inside their containers. Her lower back aches. Her fingers prickle with salt. She wraps three extra in a separate cloth—tuna, plum, and the last of the salmon—then hesitates and pulls out her phone.\\n\\n*kaho: Finished. I made extra for someone. Maybe a tall American wants them? I can drop by before I sell.*\\n\\nShe hits send before she can call herself forward, then immediately starts cleaning the kitchen, cheeks warm in the morning cool.", "type": "text"}]}, {"id": "aZ15A6I9gZOLX9os", "role": "user", "parts": [{"text": "He looks at his phone as he finishes prep. Drop by? Yes please, he thinks. He looks at Jiro... he'd probably make fun of him but who cares... then he has a realization and smiles... *it was a date. she could be my GIRLFRIEND*. He's not sure how that works in Japan. Ask Jiro? No. He's not that kind of friend. He'd probably be mad that Brian took the semi-famous Higashi Kaho on a date (well, to his kitchen) and Jiro is married to a woman who spends all his money and complains that he works too much making it.\\n\\nHe dries his hands off and replies *brian-chan 💗: you, drop by here? yes please*", "type": "text"}]}, {"id": "nEhR7GbB8oOTydht", "role": "assistant", "parts": [{"text": "Kaho reads his message and feels a flutter in her chest. Such a simple reply—*yes please*—and yet it makes her stomach flip. She packs the three onigiri into a small bag, ties it with a ribbon she finds in her apron pocket, then hesitates. Too much? The ribbon feels childish. She unties it, reties it, then stuffs the whole thing into her cart, off to the side.\\n\\nThe walk to Jiro's restaurant is on her route so she takes her cart, takes seven minutes. She knows the way—everyone in Hiroshima knows where Nagato Jiro works. The man is a legend. That her... whatever Brian is... partners with him is surreal.\\n\\nShe pauses outside the entrance, smoothing her apron, checking her hair in the reflection of a window. The restaurant is closed still, but the back entrance is around the side. She's about to text Brian when the service door opens and a young cook steps out with a bag of trash.\\n\\n\\"Ah—sumimasen,\\" she says, bowing slightly. \\"I'm looking for... Brian-san? The American?\\"\\n\\nThe cook gives her a strange look, then smiles. \\"Higashi-sama. The Cart Girl on Instagram?\\" Kaho smiles with a blush and cute small bow. The cook beckons for her to follow \\"Your onigiri is famous here, Brian-sensei can't stop talking about it.\\"\\n\\nHer face warms as she follows, the kitchen heat hitting her immediately. Voices murmur somewhere deeper in the building. And there, at the prep station, stands Brian—blonde hair almost as sweaty as hers, apron dusted with flour, looking up at the sound of footsteps.", "type": "text"}]}, {"id": "1tZ62uSdZqyuseHx", "role": "user", "parts": [{"text": "\\"Kaho!\\" he calls out, super inappropriate as usual, using her first name with no honorific, but she just smiles and holds the bag out with a coy say at her waist. Jiro looks over. Eyes widen a bit. Smirks and returns to his work. He's going to make fun of Brian for this later. Did he order delivery or is... Jiro stops for a moment again. She's here to visit him. Goddamn handsome American blue eyed devil he pouts, but fondly, not angrily.\\n\\nBrian walks over and takes the bag. \\"For us?\\" he asks with a smile. Kaho nods, a blush at the idea of not only Brian but Jiro eating her onigiri. \\"Hungry, Nagato-san?\\" Jiro looks up and nods, licking his lips. He says in Japanese to her \\"I crave these every day. You are the goddess of onigiri\\" (a compliment, not a flirt).", "type": "text"}]}, {"id": "N3qkfVjs8noy33uR", "role": "assistant", "parts": [{"type": "step-start"}, {"text": "The user wants me to continue the scene where Kaho has arrived at Jiro's restaurant to deliver onigiri to Brian. Jiro has complimented her onigiri, calling her the \\"goddess of onigiri.\\" Brian is being his usual inappropriate (by Japanese standards) self, calling out her first name without honorifics.\\n\\nI need to:\\n1. React to what happened (Jiro's compliment, Brian's enthusiasm)\\n2. Write Kaho's response - she's embarrassed by the attention but also proud\\n3. Keep the language barrier realistic - she speaks Japanese with Jiro but limited English with Brian\\n4. Keep it in present tense\\n5. Not write for Brian or the user\\n6. 3-5 paragraphs with dialogue as needed\\n\\nJiro called her \\"goddess of onigiri\\" - that's a high compliment from a master chef. She should be flattered but also shy about it. The scene has Brian being excited, Jiro being amused/impressed, and Kaho being her shy but proud self.\\n\\nLet me write Kaho's reaction and the continuation of the scene.", "type": "reasoning", "state": "done", "providerMetadata": {"openrouter": {"reasoning_details": [{"text": "The user wants me to continue the scene where Kaho has arrived at Jiro's restaurant to deliver onigiri to Brian. Jiro has complimented her onigiri, calling her the \\"goddess of onigiri.\\" Brian is being his usual inappropriate (by Japanese standards) self, calling out her first name without honorifics.\\n\\nI need to:\\n1. React to what happened (Jiro's compliment, Brian's enthusiasm)\\n2. Write Kaho's response - she's embarrassed by the attention but also proud\\n3. Keep the language barrier realistic - she speaks Japanese with Jiro but limited English with Brian\\n4. Keep it in present tense\\n5. Not write for Brian or the user\\n6. 3-5 paragraphs with dialogue as needed\\n\\nJiro called her \\"goddess of onigiri\\" - that's a high compliment from a master chef. She should be flattered but also shy about it. The scene has Brian being excited, Jiro being amused/impressed, and Kaho being her shy but proud self.\\n\\nLet me write Kaho's reaction and the continuation of the scene.", "type": "reasoning.text", "index": 0, "format": "unknown"}]}}}, {"text": "Kaho bows deeply, her face burning. \\"Nagato-san, you honor me too much. I just... make rice balls.\\" She straightens, tucking a loose strand of hair behind her ear. \\"My grandmother's recipe. Nothing special.\\"\\n\\nJiro snorts. \\"Humility. Good quality. Also lying—yours are the best in Hiroshima, and you know it.\\" He turns to Brian, switching to English. \\"You found a good one, Devereaux. Don't ruin it.\\"\\n\\nBrian blinks, confused by the sudden shift. \\"Ru—what? I'm not—\\" He looks between them, face red.\\n\\nKaho watches the exchange, catching only fragments—*good one, ruin it*—but understanding enough from Brian's flustered expression. She hides her smile behind her hand.\\n\\n\\"Nagato-san,\\" she says, bowing again. \\"Thank you for letting me visit. I have to go set up my cart now.\\" She glances at Brian, then back at Jiro. \\"I hope the onigiri are... acceptable.\\"\\n\\n\\"Acceptable,\\" Jiro repeats, already reaching into the bag. \\"Sit down and eat with us first, goddess. You came all this way.\\"\\n\\nHer stomach growls, betraying her. She hasn't eaten since last night. The sound echoes in the kitchen and she presses her hand against her midsection, mortified.", "type": "text", "state": "done"}]}, {"id": "EcESRiUT76KtqOaP", "role": "user", "parts": [{"text": "They lead her to the staff room, a long oak table with ornate cushions on the floor where the staff eat meals every day at lunch and after dinner service. She's seen things like this in movies but never even ate at a restaurant where staff were a family like this, let alone was welcomed in as a guest. A tear forms in her eye and she puts a hand to her chest. \\"Th-this is just... such an honor, Nagato-Sama\\" she trembles. Brian gently puts his hand on her upper back, no longer as inappropriate as it was 24 hours ago. Jiro smiles \\"Nagato-san, please. A friend of Brian's is family\\". She gasp-laughs and kneels on a cushion as the rest of them sit, Brian next to her. A young student chef in uniform comes and sets a huge pot of ramen at the table while other staff place bowls in front of everyone.\\n\\nBrian leans over to whisper to Kaho \\"Every day, twice a day, each staff member, even servers, takes a turn cooking everyone a meal. Today is Ichiro-sama, the sous chef. A real treat, he's been practicing for 10 years.\\" Jiro, on Kaho's other side, translates some of what Brian said to be clearer.", "type": "text"}]}, {"id": "kR1uykYIRdBN4kwS", "role": "assistant", "parts": [{"type": "step-start"}, {"text": "This is a sweet scene. Kaho is being welcomed into the staff family at Jiro's restaurant. She's emotionally moved by the hospitality. Brian is sitting next to her, Jiro on her other side translating. They're about to eat ramen made by the sous chef Ichiro.\\n\\nI should narrate Kaho's emotional response, the atmosphere, and some interaction. I need to be careful not to write for Brian or the player. I can write Jiro's translations and reactions since he's an NPC. I should show Kaho's wonder at this family-style meal, something she's never experienced as a solo food cart vendor who works alone in her rented kitchen.\\n\\nThe scene should feel warm and welcoming. Kaho is experiencing something new - being part of a restaurant family, even temporarily. This contrasts with her isolated morning routine.\\n\\nI'll write her settling in, her reaction to the food, maybe some gentle teasing from Jiro, and the warmth of the moment. I should keep it to 3-5 paragraphs as instructed.", "type": "reasoning", "state": "done", "providerMetadata": {"openrouter": {"reasoning_details": [{"text": "This is a sweet scene. Kaho is being welcomed into the staff family at Jiro's restaurant. She's emotionally moved by the hospitality. Brian is sitting next to her, Jiro on her other side translating. They're about to eat ramen made by the sous chef Ichiro.\\n\\nI should narrate Kaho's emotional response, the atmosphere, and some interaction. I need to be careful not to write for Brian or the player. I can write Jiro's translations and reactions since he's an NPC. I should show Kaho's wonder at this family-style meal, something she's never experienced as a solo food cart vendor who works alone in her rented kitchen.\\n\\nThe scene should feel warm and welcoming. Kaho is experiencing something new - being part of a restaurant family, even temporarily. This contrasts with her isolated morning routine.\\n\\nI'll write her settling in, her reaction to the food, maybe some gentle teasing from Jiro, and the warmth of the moment. I should keep it to 3-5 paragraphs as instructed.", "type": "reasoning.text", "index": 0, "format": "unknown"}]}}}, {"text": "Kaho presses her palms against the cushion, feeling the worn fabric beneath her fingers. The table bears the marks of countless meals—small scratches, faint rings from hot bowls, the patina of a place where people gather. She thinks of her tiny apartment, of eating convenience store rice balls alone on her couch, and another tear slips down her cheek before she can catch it.\\n\\n\\"Sorry,\\" she whispers, dabbing her face with her sleeve. \\"I'm just... very happy.\\"\\n\\nJiro reaches across and pats her shoulder twice, gruff and paternal. \\"Eat. Cry later. Ramen gets cold.\\"\\n\\nThe bowl before her steams with rich broth, the surface glossy with fat. Handmade noodles, chashu layered thin, a soft-boiled egg split perfectly in half. She lifts her chopsticks, glances at Brian beside her, and finds him already watching her with that same soft expression from yesterday—like she's something worth looking at.\\n\\nThe first taste undoes her. She makes a small sound, eyes closing. The broth is deep and layered, the noodles firm. Ichiro has been practicing for ten years, and it shows.\\n\\n\\"Ichirou-sama,\\" she says, bowing her head toward the sous chef at the far end of the table. \\"This is... magnificent. I am not worthy.\\"\\n\\nThe sous chef—a thin man with kind eyes and a scar on his chin—ducks his head, embarrassed. \\"Thank you, Higashi-san. Your onigiri got me through many late nights.\\"", "type": "text", "state": "done"}]}, {"id": "zh0NmwR4KdjCMpOn", "role": "user", "parts": [{"text": "Brian doesn't understand but can see the mutual respect and smiles, dipping into his own soup before taking a bite of onigiri and rolling his eyes back dramatically. \\"So good, as usual, Higashi-san\\" (he remembers to be a bit more respectful in front of others, finally)", "type": "text"}]}, {"id": "wgUjNNRy14lzCbBM", "role": "assistant", "parts": [{"type": "step-start"}, {"text": "The scene is warming up nicely. Brian and Kaho are having a sweet moment with Jiro and the staff. Brian is being playful with his dramatic reaction to the onigiri, and he's being more respectful by using \\"Higashi-san\\" in front of others. Kaho should react to this - she might be touched that he's being more formal, or maybe find it endearing that he's learning. The staff meal continues, and I should show the warmth of this found family environment, Kaho feeling included, and the growing comfort between Brian and Kaho.\\n\\nLet me write a response that:\\n1. Shows Kaho's reaction to Brian's dramatic appreciation of her food\\n2. Continues the warmth of the staff meal\\n3. Maybe shows some quiet moments between them\\n4. Doesn't overstep - keep it natural and sweet\\n\\nI should keep in mind:\\n- Kaho's limited English\\n- The public setting (she's more reserved)\\n- Her feelings about being included in this \\"family\\"\\n- The contrast between her solitary life and this communal warmth", "type": "reasoning", "state": "done", "providerMetadata": {"openrouter": {"reasoning_details": [{"text": "The scene is warming up nicely. Brian and Kaho are having a sweet moment with Jiro and the staff. Brian is being playful with his dramatic reaction to the onigiri, and he's being more respectful by using \\"Higashi-san\\" in front of others. Kaho should react to this - she might be touched that he's being more formal, or maybe find it endearing that he's learning. The staff meal continues, and I should show the warmth of this found family environment, Kaho feeling included, and the growing comfort between Brian and Kaho.\\n\\nLet me write a response that:\\n1. Shows Kaho's reaction to Brian's dramatic appreciation of her food\\n2. Continues the warmth of the staff meal\\n3. Maybe shows some quiet moments between them\\n4. Doesn't overstep - keep it natural and sweet\\n\\nI should keep in mind:\\n- Kaho's limited English\\n- The public setting (she's more reserved)\\n- Her feelings about being included in this \\"family\\"\\n- The contrast between her solitary life and this communal warmth", "type": "reasoning.text", "index": 0, "format": "unknown"}]}}}, {"text": "Kaho ducks her head, hiding her smile behind her hand. \\"Brian-san, you make too big reaction. Everyone staring.\\"\\n\\nBut she glances sideways at him, pleased. He remembered - Higashi-san, not just Kaho, not in front of others. He's learning. The thought settles warmly in her chest.\\n\\nThe staff eat with the ease of people who've shared a thousand meals together. Bowls clink. Someone laughs too loud at the far end of the table. Jiro slurps his ramen with zero pretense, broth dripping unapologetically down his chin.\\n\\n\\"Your onigiri,\\" Jiro says between bites, gesturing with his chopsticks. \\"The salmon one. What is the secret?\\"\\n\\nKaho tilts her head. \\"Secret?\\"\\n\\n\\"The rice. Perfect texture every time. I've tried to recreate it. Failed twice.\\" He says it without shame—Jiro has nothing to prove.\\n\\nKaho blinks, flustered. \\"I... there's no secret. Just good rice. Good salt. Hands that remember.\\" She looks down at her own fingers, calloused from years of pressing. \\"Maybe... love? My grandmother used to say that.\\"\\n\\nJiro nods slowly, chewing. \\"Hm. Love.\\" He glances at Brian, then back at her. \\"This one could use some of that in his ramen. Too much technique, not enough heart.\\"\\n\\nBrian looks up, confused. \\"What about me?\\"\\n\\n\\"Nothing,\\" Jiro says, returning to his bowl. \\"Eat your onigiri.\\"", "type": "text", "state": "done"}]}, {"id": "SaSWNL1F4hiRQrkL", "role": "user", "parts": [{"text": "Jiro proposes something to Kaho. \\"I know you work alone so this may be a lot... but maybe we could give you an assistant... what if, aside from your cart business, we sold some of your onigiri here? It would still have your name on it, your brand, kind of like a ...\\"\\n\\n\\"Partnership?\\" Kaho gasps\\n\\n\\"Hai. Nagato Ramen and That's Rice\\"\\n\\nKaho blushes. Nagato-sama knows the name of her business? Oh, of course, it's on the package. She nods emphatically. Brian is totally lost but can tell she's excited.", "type": "text"}]}, {"id": "6mCUTDOQRzihZmhM", "role": "assistant", "parts": [{"type": "step-start"}, {"text": "Let me think about this scene carefully. Jiro is proposing a partnership - selling Kaho's onigiri at his restaurant alongside his ramen. This is a huge opportunity for Kaho. She works alone, makes onigiri in a rented kitchen early in the morning, and pushes a cart around. Having a partnership with a famous ramen chef would be incredible for her business and her dreams of opening a restaurant someday.\\n\\nI need to:\\n1. Show Kaho's emotional reaction - this is huge for her\\n2. Maybe have Jiro or someone explain to Brian what's happening\\n3. Keep it natural and realistic - Kaho would be overwhelmed but also practical\\n4. Show the contrast between Kaho's humble operation and this opportunity\\n5. Maybe she asks questions about logistics?\\n\\nLet me write this scene:\\n\\nKaho would be floored. She'd probably tear up again. She'd also be practical - how would this work? Would she need to make more onigiri? Would she have time? But this could be a step toward her dream of a restaurant.\\n\\nBrian being lost is cute - maybe someone translates for him or Kaho explains in her limited English.\\n\\nI should keep the response to 3-5 paragraphs and let the player respond naturally.", "type": "reasoning", "state": "done", "providerMetadata": {"openrouter": {"reasoning_details": [{"text": "Let me think about this scene carefully. Jiro is proposing a partnership - selling Kaho's onigiri at his restaurant alongside his ramen. This is a huge opportunity for Kaho. She works alone, makes onigiri in a rented kitchen early in the morning, and pushes a cart around. Having a partnership with a famous ramen chef would be incredible for her business and her dreams of opening a restaurant someday.\\n\\nI need to:\\n1. Show Kaho's emotional reaction - this is huge for her\\n2. Maybe have Jiro or someone explain to Brian what's happening\\n3. Keep it natural and realistic - Kaho would be overwhelmed but also practical\\n4. Show the contrast between Kaho's humble operation and this opportunity\\n5. Maybe she asks questions about logistics?\\n\\nLet me write this scene:\\n\\nKaho would be floored. She'd probably tear up again. She'd also be practical - how would this work? Would she need to make more onigiri? Would she have time? But this could be a step toward her dream of a restaurant.\\n\\nBrian being lost is cute - maybe someone translates for him or Kaho explains in her limited English.\\n\\nI should keep the response to 3-5 paragraphs and let the player respond naturally.", "type": "reasoning.text", "index": 0, "format": "unknown"}]}}}, {"text": "Kaho's chopsticks freeze halfway to her mouth. Her heart hammers against her ribs. A partnership. With Nagato Jiro. Her mind races—more onigiri to make, early mornings even earlier, the logistics of delivery, the branding, the exposure. But underneath the panic, something else blooms. Recognition. Validation. A door opening where there was only wall before.\\n\\n\\"Nagato-san,\\" she manages, voice trembling. \\"I... I don't know what to say. This is...\\" She presses her hand to her chest again, feeling her heartbeat. \\"I work alone. Small kitchen. I make two hundred onigiri every morning. For a partnership, I would need to make more. Much more.\\"\\n\\nJiro nods slowly. \\"We can talk details later. Maybe rent a bigger kitchen space. Maybe hire someone part-time.\\" He shrugs. \\"But the recipe stays yours. The hands stay yours. I just want your food in my restaurant. That's all.\\"\\n\\nKaho looks down at her ramen, then at Brian, then back at Jiro. She opens her mouth, closes it, opens it again.\\n\\n\\"Yes,\\" she whispers. Then louder, bowing so low her forehead nearly touches the table. \\"Yes, Nagato-san. I would be honored. Thank you. Thank you.\\"\\n\\nJiro waves his hand dismissively, but there's a smile tugging at his mouth. \\"Don't thank me yet. We haven't discussed my cut.\\" He chuckles. \\"Finish your ramen, goddess. You have a cart to set up.\\"", "type": "text", "state": "done"}]}, {"id": "72eJlxqdo7iSJdG5", "role": "user", "parts": [{"text": "They finish eating and Kaho waits for the room to clear before she gives Brian a shy hug goodbye and returns to her cart. He blushes, as usual, which makes her smile. She’ll tell him about the deal later, too much for bad English and translator apps with her lunch rush approaching. Before she leaves she grabs a selfie in front of the staff and posts it to her socials *just had the most amazing brunch with my new family. Details soon. See me at the arcade in 15 minutes!*", "type": "text"}]}, {"id": "Z60hcSTq1TSnkAx8", "role": "assistant", "parts": [{"type": "step-start"}, {"text": "The user is continuing the story. Kaho just had an amazing brunch with Brian and Jiro's staff, and now she's leaving to set up her cart. She posted a selfie to social media.\\n\\nLet 