aho exhales, surveying her empty display case. Sold out before one o'clock again. Her phone tells her she's made the same amount today as she did last Thursday—except last Thursday she had twenty onigiri left over.\\n\\nShe packs the tarp, locks the wheels, and begins the slow trudge home. Her calves burn. The arches of her feet throb with each step, her socks damp and clinging. The afternoon sun presses against her shoulders. Sweat pricks at her hairline despite the breeze.\\n\\nBut underneath the exhaustion, something light. She thinks about the partnership, the staff meal, the selfie with the high school girls. She thinks about Brian's face when she hugged him—that frozen half-second before his hands found her waist.\\n\\nShe pulls out her phone and opens their chat.\\n\\n*kaho: Sold out again!! Maybe I need to wake up at 3am now 😩*\\n*kaho: How was your lunch rush? Did Jiro-san make fun of you more?*\\n\\nShe sends it before she can overthink. The cart rattles behind her as she turns onto the familiar street. Two miles. Twenty-five minutes. A shower waiting at the end, and maybe—hopefully—a message from him when she arrives.", "type": "text", "state": "done"}]}, {"id": "tZBWi2ztwG6DI8lG", "role": "user", "parts": [{"text": "She feels her phone buzz on the way but commits to the walk back. At home she pulls her phone out as she kicks her dirty well worn sneakers off. \\n\\n*brian: busy day! But it was nice, especially the morning ❤️*\\n*brian: Jiro told me about his offer. Wow so proud of u*\\n*brian: he meant it when he said he can get you extra help, maybe even work out of our kitchen.*\\nShe gasps. She’s always dreamed of working in a kitchen like that.", "type": "text"}]}, {"id": "GNb8QWu2JA7YJrlT", "role": "assistant", "parts": [{"type": "step-start"}, {"text": "The user wants me to narrate Kaho's reaction to Brian's messages about Jiro's offer - specifically that Jiro mentioned potentially getting her extra help and letting her work out of \\"our kitchen\\"