it in character - she's humble but also ambitious\\n- Not write for Brian\\n\\nLet me write this scene focusing on Kaho's reaction and her texting back.", "type": "reasoning.text", "index": 0, "format": "unknown"}]}}}, {"text": "Kaho's sneakers land in the genkan with a soft thud. She stares at her phone, reading the message again. *Our kitchen.* Jiro's kitchen. A professional space with proper equipment, ventilation, prep stations. Not Yamamoto-san's borrowed corner before dawn, but a real kitchen in a renowned restaurant.\\n\\nShe sinks onto the step, phone pressed against her chest. Her socks squish damply against the floor but she barely notices.\\n\\n*kaho: Wait. THEIR kitchen? Jiro-san's kitchen?*\\n*kaho: Brian-chan this is... I can't. That's too much. He barely knows me. I'm just a cart girl.*\\n\\nHer thumbs hover. She deletes the last sentence. Too self-pitying. She tries again.\\n\\n*kaho: Are you serious? You're not joking?*\\n\\nShe pulls off one damp sock, then the other, balling them together and tossing them toward the bathroom. Her feet prickle with relief as cool air hits them. The apartment is quiet. The convenience store hum drifts up through the floor.\\n\\nHer phone sits heavy in her lap. A real kitchen. Help. A partnership with Nagato Jiro. And Brian—Brian in the middle of it all, cheering for her, proud of her.\\n\\nShe types one more message.\\n\\n*kaho: I don't know how to repay any of this. You. Jiro-san. Everything.*\\n\\nSend. She sits in the quiet apartment and waits, her bare feet cooling against the floor.", "type": "text", "state": "done"}]}, {"id": "8Q7CNPUpEoQZp8MY", "role": "user", "parts": [{"text": "*Brian: repay? You earned it.*\\nThen she sees he’s typing for a moment, probably thinking. Shy boy, she smiles. \\n*brian: I just got home. What’re you up to tonight?*", "type": "text"}]}, {"id": "l3OFwtFWSNwart0B", "role": "assistant", "parts": [{"text": "Kaho stares at the question. Tonight. Her body aches. Her hair sticks to her 