etadata": {"openrouter": {"reasoning_details": [{"text": "The user is continuing this romantic scene between Kaho and Brian. They're having a tender moment where Kaho is worried about his visa expiring and him leaving, and Brian reassures her that he won't leave her.\\n\\nI should continue the scene naturally, staying in Kaho's perspective and emotional state. This is a very intimate, vulnerable moment. I should show her reaction to his reassurance - the relief, the emotion, the depth of what he's promising.\\n\\nI need to:\\n1. Stay in character as Kaho\\n2. Show her emotional response\\n3. Not write for Brian beyond what's already established\\n4. Keep the tender, intimate tone\\n5. Maybe end on a sweet note that leaves room for the player to respond\\n\\nLet me write this response carefully, showing Kaho's vulnerability and gratitude, and the weight of his promise.", "type": "reasoning.text", "index": 0, "format": "unknown"}]}}}, {"text": "The words hit her like a wave. She stares at him, searching his face for any hint of hesitation, any crack in the promise. She finds none.\\n\\n\\"You can't know that,\\" she whispers. \\"Two years. Maybe less. You have a life in America. Family. Friends.\\" Her voice wavers. \\"I'm just... I'm a cart girl in Hiroshima. I rent a kitchen at four in the morning. I live above a convenience store.\\"\\n\\nShe gestures vaguely at the apartment around them—the sagging couch, the single window, the walls that hold her entire small life.\\n\\nBut his hand is still on her face. His eyes are still soft. He hasn't flinched.\\n\\nSomething cracks open in her chest. She makes a sound—half laugh, half sob—and buries her face against his neck. Her arms wrap around him, pulling him close, holding on like he might disappear if she lets go.\\n\\n\\"Okay,\\" she breathes against his skin. \\"Okay. I believe you.\\"\\n\\nShe stays there for a long moment, breathing him in, feeling his arms come around her back. The television murmurs forgotten. Th