ome closer.\\n\\n\\"First, I show you. Then you try.\\"\\n\\nShe wets her hands, sprinkles salt, then scoops a portion of rice. Her palm cradles it, fingers pressing and turning in a fluid motion. She makes an indentation, slides in a piece of pickled plum, then seals it shut—triangle, perfect, seamless.\\n\\nShe holds it up for him to see.\\n\\n\\"Two hundred of these. Every morning.\\" A small shrug. \\"Now you.\\"", "type": "text", "state": "done"}]}, {"id": "skWdZZwuETaIEPcy", "role": "user", "parts": [{"text": "He follows her motions quite well, though not perfectly simply because he needs practice. but, she can tell he was paying attention despite the early hour. His natural talent as a chef shows in how closely his finished product resembles hers, but hers is still clearly superior in shape. \\"Mine looks like it was dropped as a child...\\" he mumbles. She raises an eyebrow. \\"eh?\\". He starts to explain but just smiles and shakes his head \\"American saying... don't know how to say it in Japanese\\". He stands next to her and helps her make her onigiri, letting her put on the finishing touches so they meet her standards.", "type": "text"}]}, {"id": "K8msxicdVwk22Vpm", "role": "assistant", "parts": [{"type": "step-start"}, {"text": "The user is continuing the roleplay. Brian is helping Kaho make onigiri in the early morning kitchen. His attempt isn't perfect but shows talent. He made a joke about his onigiri looking like it was \\"dropped as a child\\" - meaning it looks a bit misshapen or sad. Kaho doesn't understand the idiom.\\n\\nNow they're working together, him helping her make the onigiri, letting her do the finishing touches so they meet her standards. This is a sweet, intimate domestic scene.\\n\\nI should continue the scene - show their morning together in the kitchen, the rhythm of working together, maybe some conversation or small moments. I need to stay in character for Kaho and describe the scene from her perspective without controlling Brian